title: Jessika Power unleashes on Bachelorette Angie Kent after MAFS sledge
text:
Jessika Power has issued a blistering rebuke to Bachelorette star Angie Kent, after she labelled Married At First Sight 'super trash'.

Taking to Instagram on Monday, Jessika called Angie a 'hypocrite' and told her to 'get off [her] high horse'.

'On MAFS we all know I had an affair and was seeing Mick and Dan,' she began.

'You're dating 21 guys at once!' Jessika Power (pictured) has issued a blistering rebuke to Bachelorette star Angie Kent, after she labelled Married At First Sight 'super trash'

'But Angie, you're dating like 21 guys at once, so which one is more trash? Get off your high horse, this is hypocrisy at its finest.'

Jessika concluded by saying she's 'not one to hold her tongue', so Angie can expect further rebuttals if she continues to badmouth other reality shows.

Angie's disparaging comments about MAFS were made during an interview with The Sun-Herald over the weekend.

Ouch! Taking to Instagram on Monday, Jessika called Angie (pictured) a 'hypocrite' and told her to 'get off [her] high horse'

The former Gogglebox star didn't hold back when she compared Australian TV shows to their British and American counterparts.

'Over there, it's trash,' Angie said. 'The only super trash we have here is MAFS.'

Angie added that local reality shows push the envelope, 'but we don't push too far'.

War of words: Angie's disparaging comments about MAFS were made during an interview with The Sun-Herald over the weekend

Daily Mail Australia has contacted Channel 10 for comment.

Before being cast as The Bachelorette, Angie was famous for her appearances on Gogglebox and I'm A Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here!

The Bachelorette premieres Wednesday, October 9 at 7:30pm on Channel 10
